    <b>UImap Simplified Installation Instructions</b></font><br>
    <font class=tiny><b>Date:</b> Saturday, August 10 @ 13:38:27 EDT<br><b>Topic:</b> Skins for EverQuest</font><br><br>
    </center>
    <font class="content">
    Some of you are having trouble wading through my extremely wordy attempt at humor called the "readme.txt" that was included in the zip file.
<br><br>
Because of a recent change to the UI, you don't need to copy over all the files from a skin to use mods.  Here are the simplified installation instructions:<br><br>
<b>
1. Create a new directory in the "uifiles" directory under your "EverQuest" directory.  Let's call it "uimap".<br>
2. Unzip the files from the UImap1.0b.zip file into the uimap directory.<br>
3. Enter EverQuest, then type <i>/load uimap 1</i>
<br><br>
</b>My apologies for any confusion!<br><br>
    <br><br>
